New Records: Mitchell Santner became the first New Zealand spinner to take a five-wicket haul in a men's ODI World Cup.
Key Match Events: Mitchell Santner took 5 wickets for 59 runs.
Matt Henry took 3 wickets for 40 runs.
Three New Zealand batters reached half-centuries.
Colin Ackermann scored 69 off 73 balls for Netherlands.
Trent Boult's stunning fielding effort to dismiss Bas de Leede.
Mitchell Santner's high return catch to remove Scott Edwards.
Sybrand Engelbrecht's dismissal was overturned due to an umpire's review.
Paul van Meekeren's off-cutter to dismiss Daryl Mitchell for 48.
Roelof van der Merwe's wicket of Devon Conway for 32.
Pre-Game Insights: Netherlands won the toss and chose to field first.
New Zealand made one change with Lockie Ferguson replacing James Neesham.
Netherlands made two changes with Sybrand Engelbrecht and Ryan Klein coming in.
New Zealand captain Tom Latham emphasized putting runs on the board and defending later.
Post-Match Reflections: Mitchell Santner was named Player of the Match.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Netherlands needed a record chase of 323 to win, their highest successful run chase in ODIs being 291 against Zimbabwe in 2019.
New Zealand's innings was boosted by a strong finish, scoring 50 runs off the last three overs.
